cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a framework for extra cell range expansion in a two-tier heterogeneous cellular network, which involves network architecture and design. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the energy efficiency of the proposed framework using stochastic geometry, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a control and user plane split for the heterogeneous cellular network, which involves system design and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the different data rate requirements of macrocell and small cell users, which is related to multimedia transmission. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed framework may have implications for network security and privacy, as it involves expanding the range of small cells to accommodate extra offloaded users.
